<br>
IMO a better idea would be:<br>
Any spell 20 levels higher than the targets level will only last 30 minutes (unless the duration is already less than 30 minutes).  Any spell that is 40 levels or higher than recipient will have a maximum duration of 15 minutes.  This is for ANY spell, not only those level 51 and higher.  This cap may not be exceeded, including by the addition of Extended Enhancement type focus effects and AA.<br>
<br>
This allows you to temporarily buff anyone with any spell, it doesnt matter what level they are. It allows you to be nice and buff a wandering newbie, or escort them through a dangerous zone to show them where something is located.<br>
<br>
It always bugs me when I'm playing the druid and someone asks for a SoW and I cast SoE on them and it won't land. Oooh, thats an unbalancing spell!  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8991"><br>
