<br>
In my hour of play I get at one time, I would actually be able to kill four to five mobs as opposed to one or two.  I could still kill the mobs I was hunting without KEI, I just didn't have to spend the rest of the time sitting on my arse waiting for mana to regen.  I also didn't notice any really unbalancing things in any group I was in.  In fact, it kept me viable, as I usually feel like I can't do more than one hit or I'm running out of mana quickly.  With the KEI, I could do two or three hits and actually contribute to killing the mob.<br>
<br>
It was nice not having to go back for new buffs every few minutes.  I have minimal twinkage, but the 25 plat for the spell was some of the best money ever spent.  It allowed some reasonable killing.  I can see where people would think this spell is unbalancing, but for a rarely grouping casual wizzie, this made the game much more playable with much less downtime.   I hope when taking this away, they will give us something maybe not as good, but that helps.  Otherwise, I feel very underpowered even in same level groups.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fitzroyy>Fitzroyy</A> at: 5/20/03 5:36:51 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=necridious>Necridious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 305<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/24/03 4:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: oh dear...</span><hr size=1> The only thing KEI did was make less downtime and allowed people to solo <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>slightly</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> higher level mobs.<br>
<br>
It unbalanced nothing. Downtime is not a balance issue, and many believe it is only because the Vision(tm) said that everything had to progress at a decrepit snails pace.<br>
<br>
That said, it is fact that regen effects, either for health or mana, do make even hot and heavy fighting easier. The longer an encounter lasts, the more benefit the regen effect is.<br>
<br>
There is a simple solution to eliminate/minimize downtime while not trivializing an encounter.  Make an Item/potion/Skill that completly regens mana and/or health in a single click, usefull only every 5 minutes, but not usable while in combat.  The difficulty is in what the game considers 'in combat', though with a limiter of also within 5 minutes, even a whole extra bar of life/mana won't make or break most encounters--especially once enough mana regen becomes available that your main limiting factor is aggro, not mana.<br>
<br>
I just want to re-iterate the point that EQ is a game where many people enjoy the immense amount of downtime so that they can clean house, do chores, exercise, do homework, watch TV, read books, etc...  and that in a computer game, this is just Soooo wrong, and only years of conditioning have made us think it could be any kind of normal. <p><br>
